      "title": "Ultimately, we see striking parallels, especially in how the awakening of Conqueror's Haki was set up for the \"Wings.\" Zoro and Sanji went through similar experiences to awaken their Conqueror's Haki;",
      "text": "Ultimately, we see striking parallels, especially in how the awakening of Conqueror's Haki was set up for the \"Wings.\" Zoro and Sanji went through similar experiences to awaken their Conqueror's Haki; factors like trust, facing strong opponents, and internal conflict played out exactly the same way for both of them. Oda is clearly emphasizing once again just how similar Zoro and Sanji are and that they will remain eternal rivals, always facing opponents of comparable strength. This deliberately highlights the bond between Zoro and Sanji as the crew's \"Wings.\" Zoro got his power-up, \"King of Hell\"against King. Sanji will eventually get his power-up (Conqueror's Haki) to defeat Kilingham. I find the parallels in how Oda developed this for both of them fascinating.",
